@srkukarni @jerrypeng @kramasamy @nwangtw 
We need to stop all data processing in a heron-instance and then do a checkpoint, and then recover the data processing.

More specifically:
In: https://github.com/twitter/heron/blob/c65e312c078e52222b6ea797662715dc03674b36/heron/instance/src/java/com/twitter/heron/instance/bolt/BoltInstance.java
```
    if (bolt instanceof IStatefulComponent) {
      ((IStatefulComponent) bolt).preSave(checkpointId);
    }

    collector.sendOutState(instanceState, checkpointId);
```
And:
In https://github.com/twitter/heron/blob/28478557d50718725491c2b6a631dea1dc56f485/heron/instance/src/java/com/twitter/heron/instance/spout/SpoutInstance.java
```
    if (spout instanceof IStatefulComponent) {
      ((IStatefulComponent) spout).preSave(checkpointId);
    }

    collector.sendOutState(instanceState, checkpointId);
```
We need to make sure these two blocks will not be executed concurrently with data-processing. Otherwise, we will get a dirty state.

It could be transient failure as well - let me kick off the build again. 

